Black Alloy BS (2HS) and LS (1HS) are good for there price.<br>
Shields are difficult, you will probably end up spending (on TP) 150-250p for one of the following: Cracked Darkwood Shield, Velium Round Shield, Crested Mistmoore Shield and Crustation Shell Shield.  All those are good quality shields and you will have a time upgrading from any of them.  For a cheaper shield go for either a Shiny Brass Shield (which your druid could camp for you) for a magic bash or a Chitin Shell Shield for good AC.<br>
Bronze or Banded is probably going to be your best bet for your price.  Bronze usually sells for 1 or 2 plat per ac.<br>
<br>
Some additional things to consider...<br>
<br>
Take your paladin to Lower Guk dead side and wait by the zoneline.  Tell the people that are hunting there that you are looking for Shin Gauntlets (from live shin knights) and Greaves (from dead shin knights) and eventually you will get them.  These have the same stats as medium plate and have some minor resist bonuses, but are no drop.<br>
<br>
Depending on your server Icewall Keep may be hunted frequently with the hunters leaving the no drop frosted royal vellium armor to decay.  Again, check it out with your druid first and if it is then move your pally there and see what you can get (probably will get a decent shield while you are there also).<br>
<br>
Your druid may be able to kill some of the rares in The Warrens for some nice items, nothing particularly special though.  Then head to Stonebrunt and kill Pandas, Heretics and Highland Kobolds (if you can).  Not sure what level you can kite pandas.  Heretics WILL give you a run for your money, especially if your MR isn't that good.  You can probably harmony and pull Highland Kobolds without much problem.<br>
Pandas drop claws for a quest for a good 1HS that's slightly worse then a SSOY (need 2 claws + other stuff, but the claws are the hard part).<br>
Heretics are for a quest, need 4 heads and you can get either a slight upgrade to a Savant's cap or a minor haste sash.<br>
Highland Kobolds drop Etched Iron Armor, which is just under Fine Plate in strength and gives you a nice boost to MR.<br>
<br>
If your good at navigating through hostile territory then I would say to try for Ghoulbane.  The hard part of the Highkeep piece is getting there at 5, after that its just waiting around.  Your 30 druid could probably kill the skeletons in Najena (though it would be a real fight).  The goblins in butcherblock are usually camped on my server, you would just have to wait around then.  Piece in Unrest may be a bit tough to get without Invis to Undead (ITU).  You could try to pull the ghouls from the 2nd floor with your druid in wolf form for people in the zone (with there permission) or in a group yourself.<br>
<br>
<br>
You can probably also camp the eyes in the Gorge with your druid for extra cash.  The eyes theirselves give good money with the chance of getting a PPB which sells for about 100p on my server.<br>
